fields.name: Tic-Tac-Toe
fields.description:
You probably already know how to play Tic-Tac-Toe. It's a really simple game, right? That's what most people think. But if you really wrap your brain around it, you'll discover that Tic-Tac-Toe isn't quite as simple as you think!

Tic-Tac -Toe (along with a lot of other games) involves looking ahead and trying to figure out what the person playing against you might do next.

fields.name: Portfolio
fields.description:
A Python-based portfolio is a collection of code projects, scripts, and applications that showcase a developer's skills, expertise, and creativity. Utilizing the versatility and power of Python, such a portfolio typically encompasses a diverse range of projects, including web applications, data analysis tools, automation scripts, machine learning models, and more.

In this portfolio, each project is carefully crafted to demonstrate the developer's proficiency in various Python libraries, frameworks, and best coding practices. The code is often well-structured, documented, and efficiently optimized to showcase the creator's ability to deliver high-quality solutions.

fields.name: News App
fields.short_description: Stay updated with our News App û your daily dose of news, personalized.
fields.description:
I am leading a 4-member team that developed a dynamic News App using the Django framework. The app features various news sections with flexible filtering options, all sourced from a database.
We transformed the Bootstrap template-based News App using a customized CSS style, giving it a unique and distinct appearance.
Our News App empowers registered users with personalized pages, granting them full control to effortlessly add, delete, and modify their records.
